#Threatened species bycatch hotspots in the tropical Atlantic Ocean

Repository accompanying the manuscript:

**Lerebourg C., Arnaud L., Sabarros P.S., March Morla D., Travassos Tolotti M., Meynard C.N., Kaplan D.M.**

*Threatened species bycatch hotspots in the tropical Atlantic Ocean*

## Overview

This repository contains the R scripts used to reproduce the analyses and figures presented in the manuscript.
The study investigates bycatch communities associated with tropical tuna purse seine fisheries in the eastern tropical Atlantic Ocean. Using observer data collected aboard the French purse seine fleet between 2013 and 2022, we identify recurrent bycatch assemblages, characterize the community of threatened species, and locate persistent bycatch hotspots with potential conservation significance.

The analyses include:
* data preparation and filtering;
* descriptive analyses of bycatch composition;
* community analyses (NMDS, hierarchical clustering and co-occurrence networks);
* hotspot identification;
* biological analyses of species composition, sex ratio and life stage;
* production of the figures and supplementary tables presented in the manuscript.

## Repository structure

```text
R/                R scripts used for the analyses
figures/          Figures generated by the scripts
```

## Data availability

The observer dataset used in this study contains confidential fisheries information and cannot be publicly distributed.
Access requests should be addressed to the **Ob7 Pelagic Ecosystem Observatory (IRD)**.
The repository therefore does not include the original data used in the publication.

## Software

Analyses were performed in **R**.
Main packages include (non-exhaustive):
* vegan
* igraph
* tidyverse
* circular
* sf
* ggplot2

